"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-04-10-banyana-bayanas-failure-to-qualify-for-olympics-setback-for-womens-football-in-south-africa-ellis\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Desiree Ellis admitted that the Banyana Banyana's failure to qualify for the Olympics is a setback for women's football in South Africa.  The African champions were held to a 0-0 draw by Nigeria in Pretoria on Tuesday night.  The result was not enough to see them through with the Super Falcons having won the first leg 1-0 in Abuja last week.  'It's a big disappointment not just for us but for everyone involved in women's football because we did not go in 2020, we were in a similar situation where we had so many chances to - but did not go to the next round.  \\\"Likewise we did not go to the Olympics because of this, it will take a while to recover from this though,\\\" said Ellis.  Banyana Banyana will now shift attention to the defence of their WAFCON title this summer.  EPL: Man Utd could qualify for Champions League if they finish 6th  Paris 2024: Super Falcons will shine at Olympics - Oparanozie  UCL: South Africa's Bartlett blames Galatasaray's 4-0 defeat to Liverpool on Osimhen's injury  South Africa: Ndah still awaiting work permit to debut for Stellenbosch FC  Nigeria, South Africa strengthen military ties to tackle terrorism, modern threats  2026 World Cup: 'FIFA's decision against South Africa came very late' - Gaye tells Nigeria to be patient  Family of Plateau student murdered in South Africa seeks help to repatriate body  South Africa's Kaizer Chiefs told to appoint Nigeria's Sunday Oliseh as head coach  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"